  "decision_conditions": [
    "&lt;p&gt;The proposed mix of units by reason of no provision of 3 bed units and only 1 and 2 bed units only, fails to meet the housing need of the Borough and supply a policy compliant mix of unit, contrary to Policy H10 (Housing Size Mix) of the London Plan (2021) and Policy LP14 (Dwelling Size Mix) and LP19 (Residential Conversions) of the Hackney Local Plan (2020) and the Housing Supplementary Planning Guidance of the Mayor of London (2016).&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;",
    "&lt;p&gt;The proposed development, in the absence of a legal agreement to secure a contribution towards affordable housing fails to deliver the maximum reasonable amount of affordable housing and is therefore contrary to policy H4 (Delivering affordable housing) of the London Plan (2021), policy LP13 (Affordable housing) of Hackney’s Local Plan 2033 (2020) and Hackney&#x27;s S106 Planning Contributions SPD (2020).&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;",
    "&lt;p&gt;The proposed development, in the absence of a legal agreement to secure car-free housing, would be likely to promote the use of non-sustainable modes of transport and contribute to air pollution and congestion in the surrounding area, contrary to policies T6 (Car Parking) of the London Plan (2021), policy LP45 (Parking and Car Free Development) of Hackney’s Local Plan 2033 (2020) and Hackney&#x27;s S106 Planning Contributions SPD (2020).&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;",
    "&lt;p&gt;The proposed development, in the absence of a legal agreement to contribute towards the Carbon Offset Fund,&amp;nbsp; would fail to meet the London Objective of being a zero-carbon city by 2050, contrary to policies SI 2 (Minimising greenhouse gas emissions) of the London Plan (2021), policy&amp;nbsp; LP55 (Mitigating Climate Change) of Hackney’s Local Plan 2033 (2020) and Hackney&#x27;s S106 Planning Contributions SPD (2020).&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;",
    "&lt;p&gt;The proposed development, due to its siting, scale, and massing, has an unacceptable impact on the amenity of No. 145a Homerton High Street. Specifically, its proximity and height lead to significant overshadowing, loss of outlook, and reduced daylight and sunlight for this neighboring property. As a result, the development does not comply with Policy LP2 (Development and Amenity) of the Hackney Local Plan 2033 and the Residential Extensions and Alterations SPD&lt;/p&gt;"
  ],
